      • SimpleCompletedFuture

        public SimpleCompletedFuture(E result)
        Creates a completed future with the given result. The result can be null.

        Note: If the result is an instance of Throwable, this future will be completed exceptionally. That is, get() will throw the exception rather than return it.

      • andThen

        public void andThen(ExecutionCallback<E> callback)
        Description copied from interface: ICompletableFuture
        Registers a callback that will run after this future is completed. If this future is already completed, it runs immediately.

        Please note that there is no ordering guarantee for running multiple callbacks. It is also not guaranteed that the callback will run within the same thread that completes the future.

        Specified by:
        andThen in interface ICompletableFuture<E>
        Parameters:
        callback - the callback to execute

      • andThen

        public void andThen(ExecutionCallback<E> callback,
                    Executor executor)
        Description copied from interface: ICompletableFuture
        Registers a callback that will run with the provided executor after this future is completed. If this future is already completed, it runs immediately. The callback is called using the given executor. Please note that there is no ordering guarantee for executing multiple callbacks.
        Specified by:
        andThen in interface ICompletableFuture<E>
        Parameters:
